IaaSs provide the ability for customers to "tag" VMs, databases and other resources with custom labels and metadata values. 
Apply one or more tags to your clusters to simplify organizing, managing, searching for, and filtering resources within your IaaS-provided management console and other tools.  

To apply tags to VMs in your cluster, specify the tags in your `pks` command line as a comma delimited list of `key:value` pairs.  

For example:

<% if current_page.data.pkscommand == "create" %>
<pre class="terminal">
$ pks create-cluster my-cluster --tags status:billable
$ pks create-cluster my-cluster --tags status:non-billable,region:northwest
</pre>
<% else %>
<pre class="terminal">
$ pks update-cluster my-cluster --tags client:tinymegacorp
$ pks update-cluster my-cluster --tags client:perish.com,costcenter:pettycash
</pre>
<% end %> 

<p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: <%= vars.product_short %> supports tagging on Azure only.
</p>

